{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d9ce05ba-6e26-455d-8891-18bec4b9d8b8","content":"Here's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\nOptions after `--` are forwarded to the new platform runner. You'll also need:\n\n**NuGet packages** (add to the test project):\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`\n\n**Project property** (`.csproj` or `Directory.Build.props`):\n```xml\n<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n```\n\n**Key mapping:**\n\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n`--filter` stays the same and is handled before the `--` separator.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"55b2b391-94cc-4fcd-83b0-5737d2f1d8c2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing tooling migration, not a codebase task.\n\nLet me provide the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\nKey differences:\n- `--filter` → `--filter` (same)\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx` (built-in)\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--collect-coverage` with Microsoft.CodeCoverage (or use coverlet)\n\n\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump` and `--blame-hang` / `--blame-hang-timeout` → `--hangdump` / `--hangdump-timeout`\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform, `dotnet test` still works if you enable `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` in your project file, and the command-line arguments map similarly to the VSTest equivalents.\n\nWhen using `dotnet test` with the newer platform, I pass platform-specific options after `--`, though the exact flags depend on which extensions are registered. The migration looks like running `dotnet test` with standard filters followed by platform options like `--report-trx`, `--coverage` with format specification, and the dump flags. For .NET 8 specifically, I need to add the Microsoft.Testing.Platform packages and configure the project properties accordingly. They also need to set `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` in their project file or Directory.Build.props to enable the full integration with `dotnet test`.","outputTokens":1088,"requestId":"CFC1:1EB7:1BA6A55:1F96AF7:69EC0F2D"},"id":"d4c8e65f-761d-4cbf-b732-865de9a85090","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:48:00.564Z","parentId":"751d7597-8fb1-49a2-9ec7-f33b9a0eb5b1"}
